The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at an event honoring members of the Hispanic American Police Command Officers Association (HAPCOA). Pence expresses gratitude for the service of law enforcement officers and congratulates the honorees at the event. He highlights the bravery and sacrifice of law enforcement officers, using the story of a centurion in the Bible as an example. Pence then introduces the recipient of the Aguila Statue Award, Special Agent in Charge Hector Hernandez, and praises his career in law enforcement and his dedication to his family. Pence concludes by presenting Hernandez with the award.